# Velora Studio (Aether Interior)

Premium interior design studio landing page — elegant, minimal, editorial.

## Stack
Pure HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. No framework, no build step.

## Structure
```
velora-studio/
│
├── index.html
├── README.md
├── favicon.ico
│
├── assets/
│   ├── css/
│   │   ├── style.css        (base styles, tokens, layout)
│   │   └── responsive.css   (media-query breakpoints, loaded after style.css)
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── main.js
│   └── images/              (placeholder — hero & project imagery currently hotlinked from Unsplash)
```

## Design tokens
- **Background** `#F7F5F2` · **Text** `#181818` · **Secondary** `#6F6F6F` · **Accent** `#A98C64`
- **Display type** Cormorant Garamond · **Body type** Inter
- Generous whitespace, hairline dividers, no rounded-corner cards, no drop shadows.

## Signature interactions
- **Hero** — layered motion: scroll parallax on the background image plus a
  subtle (~2%) mouse-move shift, on top of the big editorial headline.
- **Featured Project** — full-bleed image with an overlaid caption and a
  "View Case Study" link, sitting right after the hero.
- **Services & Selected Projects** — both use the same NOVR-style
  cursor-following image preview; hovering a row shifts the label 10px,
  tints it gold, and floats a live thumbnail next to the cursor.
- **Process** — hovering a step grows a gold line across the top border and
  scales up the roman-numeral index.
- **About stats** — the numbers count up from zero once scrolled into view.
- **Footer** — doubles as a closing CTA ("Let's design your next space.")
  with direct email/phone/Instagram links above the standard nav + copyright.

## Sections
Hero → Featured Project → About Studio → Services → Selected Projects →
Design Process → Testimonials → Contact → Footer

## Running locally
Just open `index.html` in a browser — no server or build tools required.
Swap the Unsplash URLs in `index.html` for your own photography before launch.
`style.css` holds the base design; `responsive.css` holds only breakpoint
overrides, so mobile/tablet tweaks stay isolated from the core layout.

## Notes
- Animations are intentionally minimal: scroll reveals, a subtle hero/featured
  image zoom, and hover states. Nothing fires on load beyond the hero.
- Fully responsive down to mobile, with a slide-in nav menu under 720px.
- Respects `prefers-reduced-motion`.